.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-4-10::.
City: boston, berlin, colone, hamburg
The people grow 4 different varities of flowers: iris, azalea, marigold, balloon-flower
4 different pets are kept: dog, horse, lizard, mouse
 1. the owner of the lizard is on the left or right of the person traveling to colone##3
 2. the person who growsiris is on the far left or far right##3
 3. the owner of the horse is on the right of the person traveling to berlin##1
 4. the person who growsmarigold is between the person traveling to berlin and the person traveling to boston##2
 5. the owner of the mouse is on the left or right of the person traveling to berlin##3
 6. the owner of the mouse is the person traveling to colone##1
 7. the person who growsballoon-flower is on the far right##1
 8. the person traveling to boston is in an odd position##4
 9. the person who growsazalea is between the person traveling to hamburg and the person traveling to colone##2
10. the owner of the lizard is on the far left##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |    2     |     3      |    4    |
| City   | boston  | colone    | berlin | hamburg    |
| Flower   | iris | marigold | azalea  | balloon-flower |
| Pet           | lizard   | mouse    | dog        | horse   |

